    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="677"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1115/999: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Barcelona</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Franklin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-25T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 25, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 23, 7 p.m., requesting that you be furnished with 30 gas masks. From
                    the inception of the revolution in Spain, we have constantly and persistently
                    urged American nationals to depart to places of safety. At a very considerable
                    expense we have made available American naval and commercial vessels to evacuate
                    our nationals. We have urged that all our nationals who can possibly do so take
                    advantage of these facilities. We have pointed out that those American nationals
                    who remain in Spain do so at their own risk and upon their own responsibility. I
                    feel that any decision to provide gas masks would necessarily be interpreted as
                    a reversal of our policy of urging Americans who can possibly do so to leave
                    Spain.</p>
                <p>In a separate telegram today<note n="3" xml:id="d677fn3">Not printed.</note> we
                    gave you discretionary authority temporarily to close your office and to
                    evacuate with the American members of your staff if in your judgment it became
                    unsafe for you to remain.</p>
                <pb facs="0784" n="685" xml:id="pg_685"/>
                <p>In these circumstances it is not deemed advisable to comply with your
                    request.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
